<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id780326c0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ooo"><num value="460ooo">§ 460ooo.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of this subchapter, the following definitions apply:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id780326c1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ooo/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> Conservation Area</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Conservation Area” means the Las Cienegas National Conservation Area established by section 460<i>ooo</i>–3(a) of this title.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id780326c2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ooo/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> Acquisition Planning District</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Acquisition Planning District” means the Sonoita Valley Acquisition Planning District established by section 460<i>ooo</i>–1(a) of this title.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id780326c3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ooo/3"><num value="3" class="bold">(3)</num><heading class="bold"> Management plan</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “management plan” means the management plan for the Conservation Area.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id780326c4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ooo/4"><num value="4" class="bold">(4)</num><heading class="bold"> Public lands</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “public lands” has the meaning given the term in <ref href="/us/usc/t43/s1702/e">section 1702(e) of title 43</ref>, except that such term shall not include interest in lands not owned by the United States.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id780326c5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ooo/5"><num value="5" class="bold">(5)</num><heading class="bold"> Secretary</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id780326c6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/538/s1">Pub. L. 106–538, § 1</ref>, <date date="2000-12-06">Dec. 6, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2563">114 Stat. 2563</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
